"EarojaA='u", "text_ar": "عَرْجَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EurojN", "text_ar": "عُرْجٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EurojaAnN", "text_ar": "عُرْجَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, K.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aEoraju", "text_ar": "الاَعْرَجُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is an appellation of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The crow;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, K;) [and] so"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aEowaru AlA^aEoraju", "text_ar": "الاَعْوَرُ الاَعْرَجُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": because of its hopping, or leaping in going, as though shackled. (A, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEarojaA='u", "text_ar": "العَرْجَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is an appellation of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The female hyena:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, K:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EurojN", "text_ar": "عُرْجٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": the male is not called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEoraju", "text_ar": "اَعْرَجُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) And ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Euroju", "text_ar": "عُرْجُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", determinate, and imperfectly decl., means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The female hyenas,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so called as though they were a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qabiylap", "text_ar": "قَبِيلَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or tribe]; (Sh, O, K;) and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EuraAju", "text_ar": "عُرَاجُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", likewise determinate, and imperfectly decl.: (K:) or, accord. to IAar, in the phrase ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^abonaA='u Euroja", "text_ar": "اَبْنَا=ءُ عُرْجَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in a verse of Aboo-Muk'it ElAsadee, the poet makes the latter word, which is a pl., imperfectly decl. because he means"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alt~awoHiyd", "text_ar": "التَّوْحِيد"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAlEurojap", "text_ar": "وَالعُرْجَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; as though he regarded it as a sing. [proper] name: (L: [i. e., accord. to Ibr D, because he uses"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Euroja", "text_ar": "عُرْجَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as a sing. proper name, curtailed by poetic license from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEurojap", "text_ar": "العُرْجَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": if so, this last word seems here to signify a personification of lameness:]) and accord. to him (i. e. IAar), one says ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*ihi EuraAju", "text_ar": "هٰذِهِ عُرَاجُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "This is the female hyena"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[not hyenas]; the latter word imperfectly decl. (O.) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aEoraju", "text_ar": "الاَعْرَجُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also an appellation of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain deaf, malignant serpent."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) [See also the next paragraph.] ―         -b5-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEuroju", "text_ar": "العُرْجُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Three nights of the first part of the lunar month:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[perhaps in allusion to the curved aspect of the moon; though on this ground it might also be applied to three nights of the last part:] mentioned on the authority of Th. (TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "Msb", "K", "O"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}